    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-10-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-10-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="407" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d407">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Bigelow</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 293.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-10-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 30, 1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have your despatch of October 6, <hi rend="smallcaps">No.</hi> 180. While you have very properly given us
                            the inferences which you drew from the conversation of Mr. Drouyn de
                            Lhuys, which was elicited by the reading of my despatch of September 6,
                            you have, at the same time, implied that he would probably return to the
                            subject at a later day. The President waits with very considerable
                            interest for the views of the French government. Whatever has occurred
                            in connexion with the subject since my despatch was written has tended
                            to enhance that interest.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Bigelow,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
